5 OMG! I'm hooked on the fried pizza. Don't judge. It's DELICIOUS!   When we were in southern Italy a few summers ago, we enjoyed panzerotti -- blurring cultures for the sake of description: they taste like a fry bread empanada filled with tomato sauce, basil and loads of cheese.   I found recipes once I returned but, truth be told, I suck at frying.   Imagine my delight when I saw the fritta ($12.95) on the menu at Pomo!   Quadruple that delight when a "panzerotti" no less than FOUR TIMES the size of what I had in Puglia was delivered to my table!   With each bite, the rich flavor of the fried crust melts into the sweetest tomato sauce in the Valley, complimented by a burst of basil and stretchy, milky cheese!
